    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM DRIVE AXLES: EATON - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>FORWARD DIFFERENTIAL CARRIER</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401311">Figure 11</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401311" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401311" filename="../figg14/G1401311.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Forward Differential Carrier</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The removal of the forward carrier does not require disconnecting of the inter-axle driveline
                        and removal of the output shaft yoke assembly as most other Eaton tandems require.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Block the vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the axle lubricant.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect differential lockout air line.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect main driveline.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove axle stud nuts and axle shafts. (If used, remove lockwashers and taper dowels.)
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If necessary, loosen dowels by holding a brass drift in the center of the shaft head and
                            striking drift a sharp blow with a hammer.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Wear safe eye protection. Do not hit steel parts with a steel hammer. Parts can break and
                            cause injury.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Do not lie under carrier after fasteners are removed. Use transmission jack to support
                            differential carrier assembly prior to loosening fasteners.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bolts, nuts and lockwashers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove differential carrier assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
